      <svelte:fragment slot="summary">Title Search & Examinations</svelte:fragment>
      <svelte:fragment slot="content">Title Search is a detailed examination of public title records, including deeds, court records, property, and name indexes. Its purpose is to ensure that the seller is the legal owner and has the right to transfer ownership, as well as to discover any defects, liens, or other outstanding claims on the property that could prevent the sale. Making a thorough investigation and review of all title records is crucial to ensure there are no encumbrances on the property.</svelte:fragment>
