      <svelte:fragment slot="summary">The American Land Title Association</svelte:fragment>
      <svelte:fragment slot="content">The American Land Title Association (ALTA) provides endorsement forms used nationwide, sometimes with modifications in different regions. These endorsements offer insurance to lenders, covering losses from various matters including:

The property's title, on which the mortgage is issued, is either not in the borrower's name, subject to defects, liens, or encumbrances, or is unmarketable.
Lack of right of access to the land.
Invalidity or unenforceability of the lien created by the mortgage, not being prior to any other existing lien on the property on the policy's date, or being subject to mechanic’s liens under specific circumstances.
ALTA policy forms also cover the cost of defending insured matters against attacks. However, certain matters are excluded from or excepted in all policies, subject to various conditions.</svelte:fragment>
